  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your companion gains poor base attack bonus progression (equal to 1/2 Hit Dice, rounded down) and uses a d6 for its Hit Dice. The companion must choose the Magical Companion (form) talent as its free (form) talent, but is not required to use natural casting, and may gain a casting tradition of your choice. The companion is considered a Mid-Caster, and gains spell points equal to its Hit Dice plus its casting ability modifier.</p>\n<p>A mage companion must still spend feats to gain additional magic talents, as usual, and does not gain the two free bonus talents a caster usually gains with the casting class feature. A mage companion loses Climb and Swim as class skills but gains Knowledge (arcana) and Spellcraft as class skills. A mage companion may choose to give up the natural attacks granted by its base form to gain the Implement Bearer (form) talent as a bonus talent. This archetype cannot be combined with the mindless companion archetype.</p>\n",
